{
  "stem": "2581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I gave him this-- these bones and they were put [INAUDIBLE], you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were put under a  monument in Israel where we have [INAUDIBLE], a beautiful monument in the memory of our, you know victims of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we put these bones underneath this monument.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] It was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at that time, looking around at that place where it happened, you know, there were these Polish people that were there during the time that we came for the yahrzeit, they had told us in what a primitive way, at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The people were put on piles and put gasoline on them and burned until they built this-- these crematoria.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when I went again to visit that place in 19-- either '78 or '79, there was a big sign in front, [INAUDIBLE] describing who organized this place, Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Who-- how many people came from each town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I can't understand how a town was named there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But the Polish people did that, and they probably were given the wrong information, because they put up a city block-- a long monument that I happen to-- I have a picture that a professional photographer took for me-- for me.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And on one side of that big, tremendous monument, it says that the city of Kolo and Dabie-- because that's where Chelmno is situated between those two cities-- they have contributed money for this monument.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So on the front side, you see carved out you know, Jews spent, old and young, and the Polish sign, [POLISH] which means, we remember.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But on the back of that monument, it says, and I'll try to remember as close as I can.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It said, they brought us here from the old to the infant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They tortured us.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
